description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Advert &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Specialist Education Mental Health Practitioner to work in the Mental Health Support Team (Reflexions) with the initial 12 months being a training placement on the CYP IAPT CBT practitioner course&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Band 6 37.5hrs &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;2 posts are for Dudley Reflexions&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;3 posts are for Sandwell Reflexions&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;1 post is for Wolverhampton Reflexions&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity as part of a joint venture between CAMHS and Educational Psychology for an experienced mental health practitioner to complete one year of CBT training through the CYP Improved Access to Psychological Therapies training course and then upon completion of the course to be part of the new Children&#39;s and Young People&#39;s Mental Health Support Teams (Reflexions) in Dudley, Sandwell or Wolverhampton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The first year in post will be following the training schedule set out by Derby University although you will already be aligned to the Reflexions team, in order to give an overview of the first year the job description and person specification has been provided for the CBT training post. Upon completion of the course you will continue with the specialist educational mental health practitioner job role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Reflexions team will have the opportunity to further develop work within the field of young people’s mental health and wellbeing with a focus on development of whole school approaches to mental health and wellbeing and the development of the think family approaches within the schools environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The mental health support teams will be jointly provided by the Black Country Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust CAMHS teams and the Educational Psychology Teams and will provide CBT, guided self-help, parenting and whole school approaches.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be knowledgeable and experienced in mental health problems and psychiatric disorders and will be expected to carry out in-depth mental health assessments including risk assessments where required. The postholder will also need to be the link worker between the team and the CAMHS services to ensure that children and young people receive the most appropriate care and interventions and well as being experienced in multi-agency working. Support, advice and consultation to families/carers and other professionals involved in the life of the child/young person will also need to be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work in partnership with the Reflexions Team Leader and Clinical Lead to further develop the partnership working that is currently taking place between Education, Local Authority, CCG and the Child &amp; Adolescent Mental Health Service (CAMHS).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Reflexions Team is expected to be fully mobilised by January 2022.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should be experienced in mental health at a senior level with the required clinical skills to support the Mental Health Support Teams project. Experience of recent working with schools and delivering mental health promotional collaborative work in such an arena is vital in order to be able to fulfill the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have excellent communication skills and be able to network with other agencies such as Public Health, Clinical Commissioning Groups and Local Authorities amongst others as and when required. Applicants must also have experience of managing staff and be in position to be able to balance study and work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to an enhanced with children’s and adults barred list Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) Check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrew Westley, Clinical Lead for Dudley Reflexions on a.westley@nhs.net or Louise Twardowski, Clinical Lead for Sandwell &amp; Wolverhampton Reflexions on louise.twardowski@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date for applications&lt;/strong&gt; – 20th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews to be held&lt;/strong&gt; - 3rd December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Suitable applicants must be able to commence their post on 25th January 2021 in readiness for the start of university on 9th February 2021.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameAndrew Westley / Louise Twardowski&lt;/p&gt;
